    "citation": "Jovanovic 2016 26670371",
    "population": "[Training set] N: 88 Age: 36.88 ± 10.48 WT: 74.4 ± 14.56 [Test set] N: 30 Age: 38.9 ± 11.14 WT: 78.48 ± 16.01",
    "model_type": "PK",
    "objective": "“we explored the applicability of counter-propagation artificial neural networks (CPANNs) combined with genetic algorithm (GA) for prediction of TPM serum levels based on selected factors important for its prediction”",
    "covariates": "Tested: smoking status, co-therapy with lamotrigine, levetiracetam, valproic acid,CBZ, benzodiazepines and risperidone; daily TPM dose, renal function (eGFR), liver enzymes (AST, ALP and cholinesterase), bilirubin, albumin, total protein concentration, daily CBZ dose Included: TPM dose, renal function (eGFR) and carbamazepine",
    "observations": "TPM dose, renal function (eGFR) and carbamazepine dose significantly influenced TPM levels. Results indicate the feasibility of CPANNs combined with GA to predict TPM concentrations and to adjust relative importance of identified variability factors in population of adult epileptic patients. Results are in line with previous population PK analyses. CPANNs models can be useful to detect factors influencing drug levels even in the absence of prior knowledge on drug’s PK. The approach may be useful for initial covariate screening. Unfortunately neither structure nor parameter values were reported for the model (other than the number of neurons used).",
    "dose": "Steady-state oral doses in patients",
    "structure": "CPANNs combined with GA",
    "equations": "No structure reported, except for the use of 20 neurons",
    "parameter_values": "No parameters reported",
    "validation": "No / Yes (training and test datasets used for model building and validation)"
